For Who
    This is an auto-update script for Slackware/Linux users to install/update
Adobe Flash Player NPAPI plugin,

Aavilable distros:
    Slackware and slack-base distros

Usage:
    *Note: before execute, make sure that you won't have any other flash pkg,
otherwise you may need to uninstall it firstly.

    1. login in as root(sudo)
    2. run: ./updateFlash.sh
    3. After executing, you will found flash already installed/updated. and you
could find it by view in pkgtool or search in /var/log/package.

